- generate_fixtures.py lives at tests/trace_server/conformance/ (it imports
  only weave.trace_server.*) and writes BOTH fixture dirs; verified
  regeneration is byte-stable against the committed copies.
- Corpus identity gate added to tests/trace_server/test_contract_conformance.py
  (file-set equality + per-file byte equality); docstring retitled to cover
  both gates.
- Full corpus README lives server-side (the reference implementation side);
  tests/conformance/README.md is a short client-side pointer.
- noxfile: tests/conformance/ ADDED to the trace_no_server shard. This fixes
  a LATENT CI GAP in the original commit: the trace_server shard runs only
  -m trace_server, tests/conformance files carry no marker (except the old
  manual pytestmark on test_per_side_units.py), and no other shard included
  the path -- so test_corpus_library.py (and later test_corpus_content.py)
  were collected nowhere in CI. Now: unmarked client consumers run in the
  no-server leg; the publish test (client fixture -> transitively marked)
  runs in the server legs; server-side files are path-auto-marked by
  tests/trace_server/conftest.py.
- The manual `pytestmark = pytest.mark.trace_server` workaround is gone
  (marker docs say not to set it by hand).
- Per-side module docstrings (weave/trace/digest.py, ref_converters.py,
  weave/trace_server/digest.py) now cite their OWN side's fixture copy.
